<h3>Giving a student a chance at a brighter future.</h3>
<p>When students are awarded an educational scholarship, they are given a fair shot at success. </p><br>

<h3>Tax credit</h3>
<p>When individuals or corporations make a redirected tax payment to a tax credit scholarship foundation, they may receive up to a 33.3% percent tax credit for every rupee they redirect. Your contribution can be used to fund scholarships for students.</p>

<h3>Higher graduation rates</h3>
<p>When students receive educational scholarships, allowing them to go to the school of their choice, results in a significantly higher graduation rate. </p><br>

<p>As you can see, there are many reasons to redirect your tax payments to an educational scholarship foundation. Everyone has different causes that are near and dear to their heart, but contributing to the future success of a student has many benefits that go far beyond your initial contribution.</p>
